headlines.description: — Jrue Holiday scored a career-high 51 points, Giannis Antetokounmpo had 38 points in a triple-double and the NBA-leading Milwaukee Bucks beat the Indiana Pacers 149-136 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday has career-high 51 points, Bucks beat Pacers 149-136

headlines.description: — Cam Johnson had 31 points, Mikal Bridges scored 12 of his 27 in the fourth quarter and the Brooklyn Nets rallied to beat the Houston Rockets 123-114 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cam Johnson, Mikal Bridges carry Nets past Rockets, 123-114

events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Tom Thibodeau stuck with the same five players, three off his bench, for the entire fourth quarter of a key victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks pull away late without Randle to beat Heat 101-92

headlines.description: — Joel Embid returned from a hotly debated one-game absence because of injury and got the 76ers to 50 wins in the fewest amount of games since 2001. Maybe like Allen Iverson and the ‘01 Sixers, perhaps Embiid's next step is an MVP and a trip to the...

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — LeBron James wants to build up his stamina, and there are a couple more little things he is working on.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron James, Anthony Davis lead Lakers past Bulls 121-110

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had a season-high 36 points, Robert Covington also had a season best with 27 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Memphis Grizzlies 141-132 on Wednesday night to open a two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook has season-high 36 points, Clippers beat Grizzlies

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Rookie Jalen Williams' putback with less than a second remaining gave the Oklahoma City Thunder a 107-106 win over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Williams' late tip-in gives Thunder win over Pistons

events.name: Utah Jazz at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Talen Horton-Tucker scored a career-high 41 points and the Utah Jazz defeated the Spurs 128-117 on Wednesday night in what could have been coach Gregg Popovich’s final home game in San Antonio.
headlines.shortLinkText: Horton-Tucker's career-high 41 lead Jazz past Spurs 128-117

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — While a throng of purple-clad visiting fans were already celebrating, De'Aaron Fox was watching from the bench as the moments ticked down in Sacramento's 120-80 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings end long playoff drought with 120-80 win over Blazers

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant's a 13-time All-Star, a two-time NBA champion, a four-time league leader in scoring and has done just about everything else a player can do in the game of basketball.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker leads Suns over Timberwolves in Durant's home debut
